<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05033a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05033a">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05033a"> 33(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ to Martin <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n05033a"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">A young man had come to the brethren to be prepared for baptism, it being their pious custom to receive youths under such circumstances. The soul of this particular young man was dear to St. Martin, and great was his grief when, on returning to the monastery after an absence of some two or three days, he was told that the lad had died suddenly. <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 33</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
